            <h4>What is the current population of Belington?</h4>
            <p>
                Based on the latest 2022 data from the US census, the
                current population of Belington is 1,803.  Belington, West Virginia is the 7,984th largest city in the US.
            </p>

            

            

            <h4>What was the peak population of Belington?</h4>
            <p>
                
                    The peak population of Belington was in
                    2010, when its population was
                    1,921.
                    
                        In 2010, Belington was the
                        7,703rd largest city in the US; now
                        its fallen to the 7,984th largest city in
                        the US.
                    
                    Belington is currently
                        <span style="color: red;">
                            6.1%
                            smaller
                        </span>
                        than it was in 2010.
                    </p>
                
            </p>
            
                
                    <h4>How quickly is Belington growing?</h4>
                
                <p>
                    
                        Belington has grown
                        0.8% 
                        since the 2000.
                    


                    
                        Belington, West Virginia's growth is about average.
                        41% of similarly sized
                        cities are growing faster since 2000.
                    
                </p>
            

            

            

            

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
